So excited to announce something I am very passionate about! My wallpaper ‘Storyboards By Melora Hardin’ is finally available for purchase. I’ve always loved and created collage art since I was a kid, I love expressing myself visually and it always has kept me creatively stimulated, especially while on location in between filming scenes for The Bold Type. Each wallpaper tells a different story that hopefully will make you feel empowered and joyful. I felt compelled to share my wallpaper with all of you and I hope it brings you as much happiness as it brought me to make it. To purchase head to my website via the link in my bio!

So wonderful to have the one woman film I star in ‘Golden Vanity’ make its debut at the Burbank film festival last night!

As Golden Vanity makes its way into the world, I want to say how proud I am of playing the fierce, funny, and tragic character of Mabel Montgomery Mayflower.

Women have been there from the start, in front of and behind the camera, working to make Hollywood into the enormous industry it is today. Amongst the successes, so many have been sidelined, maligned, and subjected to savage treatment.

The industry has improved since Mabel’s day, but as we know, systemic abuses of power are far too common, and we still have a ways to go.
